title: Wall Street Breakfast April 27: Alphabet Addressing YouTube Slowdown, Investing Aggressively
author: Seeking Alpha
dc:creator: Seeking Alpha
description: The Alphabet earnings call clearly focused of attention on a dramatic slowdown in YouTube revenue growth against a very hot 2021 comparison. Microsoft Chief Executive Satya Nadella spent most of his company's fiscal third-quarter earnings talking about the success of the software giant's cloud services business. Elon Musk purchase of Twitter has $1B termination fee for both sides.
